text: The only stall in this coffee shop that is worth visiting

Their Tom yum chicken and green curry chicken is full of chicken skin. Not much meat to eat.. very disappointing.  they are generous only  when it comes to quantity of soup  ,noodles and rice, but not the ingredients...sigh.  dunno whether to give them another chance
The Basil Pork is really tasty and the garlic taste in the Kangkong is very delectable
1st Class Service and food… The Steam Sea-bass was cooked on the dot….  The Thai Mini Wing was delicious… Great meal… will be back again…
Food is authentic. Thai basil pork, Tom yum soup. Portion is pretty big as well. Very worth it! Will come back to try more dishes.
